Female
. Yellow bands on T1 and T2 interrupted or continuous; band on T3 interrupted with a small gap between lateral bands (
Fig. 15B
); scutum with L-shaped anterolateral stripe; scutellum and axillae together with four yellow spots (
Fig. 15B
); yellow stripe on mid-femur reaching or almost reaching distal end; inner side of hind tibia black; pronotal lobe yellow; obtuse projection on dorsolateral side of pronotum (
Fig. 15A
); vertex upcurled; mesepisternum normally dark (
Fig. 15B
) but in exceptional cases with a small yellow spot.
